---
const cards = [
  {
    label: 'No router config',
    body: 'Outbound WebSocket from your machine. Works behind CGNAT, dynamic IPs, IPv6-only ISPs.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Transparent relay',
    body: 'The relay forwards bytes without parsing or logging webhook bodies. Source code is public.',
  },
  {
    label: 'Cancel anytime',
    body: 'Cancel at any time. Your self-hosted recorder keeps working. You just lose the public endpoint URL.',
  },
];

const alternatives = [
  { name: 'Cloudflare Tunnel', detail: 'free, outbound, terminates TLS for you' },
  { name: 'Tailscale Funnel', detail: 'one command if you already run Tailscale' },
  { name: 'Caddy + DuckDNS', detail: 'classic if you have port 80/443 open' },
  { name: 'Reverse SSH to a VPS', detail: 'a $4 box and an autossh unit file' },
];
---

<section data-reveal class="border-b border-border-soft py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1320px] px-8">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <span class="font-mono text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-primary"> replayvod connect </span>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mb-6 max-w-[820px] text-display-2 text-balance">
      Live notifications without <span class="text-fg-muted">touching your router.</span>
    </h2>

    <p class="mb-12 max-w-[640px] text-[18px] leading-[1.55] text-fg">
      Twitch's EventSub needs a public HTTPS endpoint. Getting one at home means port forwarding, a static
      IP or dynamic DNS, and certificate management. Connect handles all of that through an outbound
      connection from your machine, so there's nothing to configure, and we
      <strong class="text-fg">never see your video files or your Twitch credentials</strong>.
    </p>

    <div class="mb-10 grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-border-soft md:grid-cols-3">
      {
        cards.map((c) => (
          <div class="bg-bg p-7">
            <div class="mb-2 font-mono text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-primary">{c.label}</div>
            <p class="m-0 text-[16px] leading-[1.55] text-fg">{c.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-xl border border-border-soft bg-surface/40 p-6">
      <div class="mb-3 font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-fg-muted">
        Self-host alternatives — all documented in the install guide
      </div>
      <ul class="m-0 grid list-none gap-x-8 gap-y-2 p-0 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {
          alternatives.map((a) => (
            <li class="flex gap-3 text-[15.5px] leading-[1.55] text-fg">
              <span class="mt-px flex-none text-primary">→</span>
              <div>
                <strong class="font-medium">{a.name}</strong>
                <span class="ml-2 text-fg-muted">{a.detail}</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
